entries.text: Hi Lee. How can I help you?
I have a question, what is an adjustable rate mortgage?
Adjustable rate mortgages typically have low initial interest rates. After the initial period, the rate adjusts to the current market conditions.
Okay, well is it better than a fixed rate mortgage?
Well, it depends. How long do you plan to own the house?
In that case I would suggest an adjustable rate mortgage. No sense in locking a rate for 30 years if you’re not going to live there that long.
Do you have any other questions?
I do have another question, can you give me a phone call?
I would be happy to speak on the phone. Please allow me just a moment
